---
import Layout from "@/layouts/Layout.astro";
import Main from "@/layouts/Main.astro";
import { SITE } from "@/config";

const title = "DraftFly";
const description = "DraftFly video showcase";
---

<Layout title={`${title} | ${SITE.title}`} description={description}>
  <Main pageTitle={title} pageDesc={description}>
    <div class="video-container">
      <div class="video-wrapper">
        <video
          id="draftfly-video"
          class="video-player"
          controls
          preload="metadata"
        >
          <source src="https://berryhilldev.us-lax-1.linodeobjects.com/ewor_draftfly_product_showcase_3.mp4" type="video/mp4" />
          Your browser does not support the video tag.
        </video>
      </div>

      <div class="video-info">
        <h2>About DraftFly</h2>
        <p class="beta-link">
          Checkout Draftly Beta Here: <a href="https://draftfly.berryhill.dev" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">https://draftfly.berryhill.dev</a> <span class="note">[Changes deployed daily, use on desktop]</span>
        </p>

        <div class="features-section">
          <h3>DraftFly: Reimagining Human-AI Collaboration in Content Creation</h3>

          <h4>The Problem with Current AI Writing Tools</h4>
          <p>Most AI writing tools today suffer from a fundamental flaw: they treat AI as a black box that spits out finished content. The typical workflow is:</p>
          <ol class="problem-list">
            <li>Enter a prompt</li>
            <li>Wait for AI to generate</li>
            <li>Copy/paste the result</li>
            <li>Start over if you don't like it</li>
          </ol>

          <p>This approach has several critical issues:</p>

          <div class="problem-section">
            <h5>❌ The "Copy/Paste Trap"</h5>
            <ul>
              <li>Users become passive consumers of AI output</li>
              <li>No meaningful interaction during creation</li>
              <li>Binary choice: accept all or reject all</li>
              <li>Endless regeneration cycles waste time and money</li>
              <li>Loss of creative control and authorship</li>
            </ul>
          </div>

          <div class="problem-section">
            <h5>❌ The "Black Box Problem"</h5>
            <ul>
              <li>No visibility into the AI's process</li>
              <li>Can't guide or correct mid-generation</li>
              <li>No way to refine specific sections</li>
              <li>Forced to accept hallucinations or inaccuracies</li>
              <li>No iterative improvement path</li>
            </ul>
          </div>

          <div class="problem-section">
            <h5>❌ The "Context Disconnect"</h5>
            <ul>
              <li>AI doesn't understand your specific needs</li>
              <li>Can't incorporate feedback naturally</li>
              <li>Each generation starts from scratch</li>
              <li>No learning from previous iterations</li>
              <li>Wastes research and good content</li>
            </ul>
          </div>

          <h4>DraftFly's Solution: Interactive AI Composition</h4>
          <p>We are fundamentally reimagining the relationship between human and AI as a collaborative composition process, not a generation-and-copy workflow.</p>

          <div class="paradigm-shift">
            <h5>✅ The Composition Paradigm</h5>
            <p><strong>Instead of:</strong></p>
            <pre class="workflow-old">Human → Prompt → AI → Copy/Paste → Done (or start over)</pre>

            <p><strong>We are enabling:</strong></p>
            <pre class="workflow-new">Human ⇄ AI ⇄ Human ⇄ AI ⇄ Human → Composed Final Product
   ↓      ↓      ↓      ↓      ↓
 Guide  Create Refine  Enhance Polish</pre>
          </div>

          <h4>How We're Engaging Users in Meaningful AI Interaction</h4>

          <div class="feature">
            <h5>1. Transparent AI Process</h5>
            <p>Unlike black-box generators, we are showing you exactly what the AI is doing:</p>
            <ul>
              <li><strong>Live progress updates:</strong> See the Research Agent gathering sources</li>
              <li><strong>Real-time status:</strong> Watch the Content Generator writing sections</li>
              <li><strong>Agent collaboration:</strong> Observe how Image Agent sources visuals</li>
              <li><strong>Step-by-step visibility:</strong> Understand the creation process</li>
            </ul>
            <p class="note-text"><strong>Why this matters:</strong> You're not waiting in the dark. You understand how your content is being created, building trust and allowing you to anticipate what's coming.</p>
          </div>

          <div class="feature">
            <h5>2. In-Context Editing (No Copy/Paste Required)</h5>
            <p><strong>Traditional tools force you to:</strong></p>
            <ul>
              <li>Copy AI output to another editor</li>
              <li>Make changes manually</li>
              <li>Lose connection to AI assistance</li>
              <li>Start over for major changes</li>
            </ul>
            <p><strong>Our approach:</strong></p>
            <ul>
              <li>Select any text directly in the interface</li>
              <li>Describe your desired change in natural language</li>
              <li>AI refactors in-place maintaining context</li>
              <li>No copy/paste - work stays in one place</li>
              <li>Iterative refinement - keep improving the same content</li>
            </ul>
            <div class="example-box">
              <p><strong>Example workflow:</strong></p>
              <ol>
                <li>AI generates: "Investing in real estate can be profitable"</li>
                <li>You select it and comment: "Make this more specific to Panama, add statistics"</li>
                <li>AI refactors: "Panama's real estate market has seen 8% annual growth since 2020, making it one of Latin America's most profitable investment destinations"</li>
                <li>Content updates in-place, maintaining all formatting and context</li>
              </ol>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="feature">
            <h5>3. Granular Control Without Starting Over</h5>
            <p>Most AI tools make you choose between:</p>
            <ul>
              <li>Accept the entire output (even if 90% is good but 10% needs work)</li>
              <li>Regenerate everything (losing the good 90%)</li>
            </ul>
            <p><strong>We are enabling surgical precision:</strong></p>
            <ul>
              <li>Edit specific sentences without touching the rest</li>
              <li>Swap individual images while keeping the text</li>
              <li>Refine particular sections independently</li>
              <li>Preserve what works while improving what doesn't</li>
            </ul>
          </div>

          <div class="feature">
            <h5>4. Multi-Variation Exploration</h5>
            <p>Instead of regenerating the same prompt hoping for better results:</p>
            <div class="comparison-box">
              <p><strong>Traditional approach:</strong></p>
              <p class="traditional">Generate → Don't like it → Regenerate → Still not right → Regenerate again...<br>(Each time losing previous work)</p>

              <p><strong>Our approach:</strong></p>
              <p class="modern">Generate 3 variations simultaneously → Compare → Pick best parts → Refine each independently<br>(All variations preserved, can mix and match)</p>
            </div>
            <p><strong>This means:</strong></p>
            <ul>
              <li>Explore different angles on the same topic</li>
              <li>Compare approaches side-by-side</li>
              <li>Cherry-pick the best from each variation</li>
              <li>No lost work - all versions saved</li>
            </ul>
          </div>

          <div class="feature">
            <h5>5. Conversational Image Curation</h5>
            <p><strong>Traditional:</strong> Browse stock photos, download, upload, insert, resize...</p>
            <p><strong>We are building:</strong></p>
            <ul>
              <li>Hover over any image</li>
              <li>Describe what you want: "modern office with plants"</li>
              <li>AI understands context + your description</li>
              <li>New image appears instantly</li>
              <li>No leaving the interface</li>
            </ul>
            <p class="note-text"><strong>The magic:</strong> AI considers both your description AND the blog content to find contextually perfect images.</p>
          </div>

          <div class="feature">
            <h5>6. Persistent Creative Workspace</h5>
            <p>Unlike disposable chat interfaces, we are creating:</p>
            <ul>
              <li>All work auto-saves to your account</li>
              <li>Resume editing anytime - load previous posts</li>
              <li>Track changes with timestamps</li>
              <li>Search your content library</li>
              <li>Build on previous work instead of starting fresh</li>
            </ul>
          </div>

          <div class="feature">
            <h5>7. Direct Publishing Integration</h5>
            <p>The final piece that eliminates copy/paste entirely:</p>
            <div class="comparison-box">
              <p><strong>Traditional workflow:</strong></p>
              <p class="traditional">AI Tool → Copy → Open CMS → Paste → Format → Add images → Configure → Publish</p>

              <p><strong>Our workflow:</strong></p>
              <p class="modern">Compose in DraftFly → Click "Publish" → Done</p>
            </div>
            <ul>
              <li>One-click publishing to your blog</li>
              <li>Metadata managed in the same interface (tags, featured status, slugs)</li>
              <li>Update existing posts without re-importing</li>
              <li>No formatting loss - what you see is what publishes</li>
            </ul>
          </div>

          <h4>The Philosophical Shift: From Generation to Composition</h4>
          <p>We are driving a fundamental shift in how we think about AI writing tools:</p>

          <div class="paradigm-comparison">
            <div class="old-paradigm">
              <h5>Old Paradigm: AI as Content Generator</h5>
              <ul>
                <li>AI does the work, human accepts/rejects</li>
                <li>Passive consumption</li>
                <li>Copy/paste workflow</li>
                <li>Disposable outputs</li>
                <li>Binary decisions</li>
              </ul>
            </div>
            <div class="new-paradigm">
              <h5>New Paradigm: AI as Composition Partner</h5>
              <ul>
                <li>Human guides, AI executes</li>
                <li>Active collaboration</li>
                <li>In-place refinement</li>
                <li>Persistent workspace</li>
                <li>Iterative improvement</li>
              </ul>
            </div>
          </div>

          <h4>Real-World Impact</h4>

          <div class="impact-section">
            <h5>For Content Marketers:</h5>
            <ul>
              <li>No more copy/paste between 5 different tools</li>
              <li>Refine content without losing progress</li>
              <li>Manage multiple variations efficiently</li>
              <li>Publish directly from composition interface</li>
            </ul>
          </div>

          <div class="impact-section">
            <h5>For Bloggers:</h5>
            <ul>
              <li>Maintain creative control throughout the process</li>
              <li>See AI's research and guide it</li>
              <li>Swap images conversationally</li>
              <li>Build a library of refinable content</li>
            </ul>
          </div>

          <div class="impact-section">
            <h5>For Agencies:</h5>
            <ul>
              <li>Client feedback integration - select and refine based on comments</li>
              <li>Version management - multiple approaches for client review</li>
              <li>Efficient workflows - no tool-switching</li>
              <li>Consistent quality - iterative refinement ensures polish</li>
            </ul>
          </div>

          <h4>The Bottom Line</h4>
          <div class="bottom-line">
            <p><strong>Most AI writing tools ask:</strong> "What do you want me to write?"</p>
            <p><strong>We are asking:</strong> "How can we compose this together?"</p>

            <p>The difference is profound:</p>
            <ul class="value-props">
              <li>✅ Meaningful engagement vs. passive waiting</li>
              <li>✅ Iterative refinement vs. regeneration loops</li>
              <li>✅ In-context editing vs. copy/paste workflows</li>
              <li>✅ Transparent process vs. black box generation</li>
              <li>✅ Persistent workspace vs. disposable outputs</li>
              <li>✅ Surgical precision vs. all-or-nothing choices</li>
              <li>✅ Direct publishing vs. multi-tool workflows</li>
            </ul>
          </div>

          <p class="conclusion">
            We aren't just generating content - we are building a <strong>collaborative composition environment</strong> where AI and human work together to create, refine, and publish content without ever leaving the interface or losing creative control.
          </p>

          <p class="conclusion">
            This is the future we are creating: not replacing human creativity, but <strong>amplifying it through meaningful, interactive collaboration.</strong>
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </Main>
</Layout>

<style>
  .video-container {
    max-width: 1200px;
    margin: 0 auto;
    padding: 2rem 0;
  }

  .video-wrapper {
    position: relative;
    width: 100%;
    margin-bottom: 2rem;
    background-color: #000;
    border-radius: 8px;
    overflow: hidden;
    box-shadow: 0 4px 6px -1px rgb(0 0 0 / 0.1), 0 2px 4px -2px rgb(0 0 0 / 0.1);
  }

  .video-player {
    width: 100%;
    height: auto;
    display: block;
    aspect-ratio: 16 / 9;
  }

  .video-info {
    margin-top: 2rem;
  }

  .video-info h2 {
    font-size: 1.875rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
    color: var(--foreground);
  }

  .video-info h3 {
    font-size: 1.5rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    margin-top: 2.5rem;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
    color: var(--foreground);
  }

  .video-info h4 {
    font-size: 1.25rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    margin-top: 2rem;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
    color: var(--foreground);
  }

  .video-info h5 {
    font-size: 1.125rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    margin-top: 1.5rem;
    margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
    color: var(--foreground);
  }

  .video-info p {
    font-size: 1.125rem;
    line-height: 1.75;
    color: var(--fg-secondary);
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
  }

  .beta-link {
    font-size: 1.125rem;
    margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
  }

  .beta-link .note {
    font-size: 0.875rem;
    color: var(--fg-tertiary);
    font-style: italic;
  }

  .features-section {
    margin-top: 3rem;
  }

  .intro {
    font-size: 1.125rem;
    line-height: 1.75;
    color: var(--fg-secondary);
    margin-bottom: 2rem;
  }

  .feature {
    margin-bottom: 2rem;
    padding: 1.5rem;
    background-color: var(--bg-secondary);
    border-radius: 8px;
    border-left: 4px solid var(--accent);
  }

  .feature ul {
    list-style-type: disc;
    margin-left: 1.5rem;
    margin-top: 0.75rem;
    margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
  }

  .feature li {
    margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
    line-height: 1.6;
    color: var(--fg-secondary);
  }

  .workflow {
    margin-top: 1rem;
    padding: 0.75rem;
    background-color: var(--bg-tertiary);
    border-radius: 4px;
    font-size: 0.95rem;
  }

  .note-text {
    margin-top: 1rem;
    padding: 0.75rem;
